Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of preserving pairwise-distances of low-complexity vectors when mapped to a finite set of vectors using a quantized and dithered random linear mapping. This involves concepts from information theory (quantization), machine learning (low-distortion embeddings), and numerical analysis (structured sets). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
